1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,462
I am Uhtred, son of Uhtred.

2
00:00:04,796 --> 00:00:10,219
My birthright Bebbanburg
was cruelly taken by my Uncle Aelfric.

3
00:00:10,302 --> 00:00:14,056
My greatest fighters...
or the most fearful?

4
00:00:14,139 --> 00:00:15,849
His men desert him

5
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:19,770
and the Scots send raiders,
who weaken those that remain.

6
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:22,105
How many did we lose this time?

7
00:00:22,564 --> 00:00:25,734
The time is right for me
fo take back what is mine.

8
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:28,320
Give me 100 men. It will take a week.

9
00:00:28,403 --> 00:00:30,697
Two hundred, I can take it in a day.

10
00:00:30,781 --> 00:00:35,911
But the new king, Edward, has fallen
under the influence of Lord Aethelhelm.

11
00:00:35,994 --> 00:00:38,872
I'm no longer the boy
who can be bent to your will!

12
00:00:38,956 --> 00:00:43,043
Aethelred of Mercia looks fo
Bebbanburg for a different purpose.

13
00:00:43,126 --> 00:00:46,672
I'm collecting all the bones
of our beloved saint as a good omen

14
00:00:46,755 --> 00:00:50,175
to signal to the Mercian people that
I shall restore their lands to greatness.

15
00:00:50,259 --> 00:00:54,137
He has sent holy men there
to bargain for an ancient relic.

16
00:00:55,264 --> 00:00:58,100
I have also sought out the help
of a Christian.

17
00:00:58,183 --> 00:00:59,560
Hello, Father.

18
00:00:59,643 --> 00:01:05,274
My son, who was taken by Alfred
and raised with a devout faith.

19
00:01:05,357 --> 00:01:07,985
The Mercian commander Eardwulf

20
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:11,488
has traveled fo East Anglia
to meet with Haesten.

21
00:01:11,572 --> 00:01:12,864
Did you see them leave?

22
00:01:12,948 --> 00:01:15,826
Yes. They're dismantling
their camp and packing their boats.

23
00:01:15,909 --> 00:01:19,997
And now Aethelred looks
to conquer Daneland

24
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:22,040
as well as Eardwulfs sister.

25
00:01:23,792 --> 00:01:27,713
The feelings that Aethelflaed
and I have always held

26
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:29,298
can no longer be contained.

27
00:01:30,257 --> 00:01:34,344
But for now, my duty draws me
fo the north once again.

28
00:01:35,012 --> 00:01:36,680
To Bebbanburg!

29
00:01:37,389 --> 00:01:39,224
Destiny is all!

30
00:02:02,289 --> 00:02:03,957
Ran can be a vixen.

31
00:02:05,709 --> 00:02:07,127
This should settle her.

32
00:02:07,586 --> 00:02:11,214
Ran is pagan lies.
I pity you for believing it.

33
00:02:11,757 --> 00:02:14,551
- Finan, give him something to do.
- Yes, Lord!

34
00:02:15,927 --> 00:02:18,680
Oh, God. Whoa.

35
00:02:19,473 --> 00:02:21,642
Hey! You can empty this.

36
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:30,275
Tell me the truth.

37
00:02:31,568 --> 00:02:33,904
- Am I the bait?
- For what?

38
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:36,406
In the plan you are hiding from me.

39
00:02:37,491 --> 00:02:40,160
- Am I the bait?
- Nothing is hidden from you.

40
00:02:40,243 --> 00:02:42,954
We are tracking monks
who have entry to Bebbanburg.

41
00:02:44,373 --> 00:02:48,001
You will befriend them, enter Bebbanburg
and open the sea gate to us.

42
00:02:48,085 --> 00:02:51,630
I think you have another reason
for dragging me into your revenge.

43
00:02:51,713 --> 00:02:54,758
Yes, so you may win honor and reputation.

44
00:02:54,841 --> 00:02:57,886
The only reputation that matters
is my standing with God.

45
00:02:59,262 --> 00:03:01,890
You cannot force a boy to be a warrior.

46
00:03:01,973 --> 00:03:05,602
My blood runs within his veins.
Why can he not see that?

47
00:03:05,686 --> 00:03:08,188
Because your blood
is that of a stubborn bastard!

48
00:03:11,483 --> 00:03:13,777
- Our Father...
- Who do you pray for, boy?

49
00:03:15,862 --> 00:03:18,281
The men you will slaughter.

50
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:22,285
You seem to take things
when you want them.

51
00:03:22,994 --> 00:03:25,455
When you do, show mercy.

52
00:03:26,164 --> 00:03:30,001
To my Uncle Aelfric,
who spent a lifetime wishing me dead?

53
00:03:30,085 --> 00:03:33,004
- There is a power in forgiveness.
- Good.

54
00:03:35,966 --> 00:03:38,176
Then you may use it to forgive me.

55
00:03:47,602 --> 00:03:51,022
He continues to sign himself
King of Mercia,

56
00:03:51,106 --> 00:03:53,608
and now we hear he leads troops
out of Aegelesburg.

57
00:03:53,692 --> 00:03:55,694
Aethelred has always been ambitious.

58
00:03:55,777 --> 00:03:59,030
- Do you know where he's gone?
- My husband doesn't inform me of anything.

59
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:02,534
I know he is seeking the bones
of St. Oswald.

60
00:04:03,452 --> 00:04:05,746
Edward, that is grave.

61
00:04:05,829 --> 00:04:10,208
If he is seeking St. Oswald,
he is seeking to break from Wessex.

62
00:04:12,335 --> 00:04:16,214
Many Mercians believe
that uniting the body of the saint

63
00:04:16,298 --> 00:04:18,675
will restore their land to greatness.

64
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:21,136
Yes, but the people want peace, not war.

65
00:04:21,219 --> 00:04:24,014
Still, it is a signal of intention.

66
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:27,267
Or a ploy to pander
to the simple folk of Mercia.

67
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:30,061
The people of Mercia are not simple.

68
00:04:31,688 --> 00:04:34,274
Well, whatever it is he is doing...

69
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:36,860
do not allow yourself to be drawn in.

70
00:04:36,943 --> 00:04:39,321
The weak should not be allowed
to set terms.

71
00:04:39,404 --> 00:04:41,990
If you do not play, he cannot win.

72
00:04:42,073 --> 00:04:45,410
Leave childishness to the little children.

73
00:04:45,494 --> 00:04:49,873
Ah. Here he is,
the future King of all the realm.

74
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:52,250
See how nimble he is!

75
00:04:53,084 --> 00:04:54,753
That's a great swordsman in the making!

76
00:04:55,378 --> 00:04:56,963
Yes, indeed.

77
00:04:57,047 --> 00:04:58,590
- Lady.
- Lord.

78
00:04:58,673 --> 00:05:02,594
Yes, and he is a child
of great authority, too.

79
00:05:03,053 --> 00:05:06,473
You should have seen the way he kicked
Steapa to make his displeasure known.

80
00:05:07,724 --> 00:05:09,184
A boy of many talents.

81
00:05:13,438 --> 00:05:14,481
Come with me.

82
00:05:14,564 --> 00:05:17,567
I want to show you
a book of your grandfather's.

83
00:05:17,651 --> 00:05:20,278
Do not pester the boy with Latin.

84
00:05:20,362 --> 00:05:23,198
He is to be a king, not a clerk.

85
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:26,034
The men of Wessex are fighters.

86
00:05:26,952 --> 00:05:29,579
Rule the sword and rule the land.

87
00:05:34,751 --> 00:05:37,462
He digs away at all that is precious.

88
00:05:37,921 --> 00:05:39,339
Yes, it is troubling...

89
00:05:40,131 --> 00:05:42,634
as are my husband's intentions.

90
00:05:43,635 --> 00:05:45,929
I will ask Aldhelm to make inquiries.

91
00:05:51,268 --> 00:05:52,310
Father Pyrlig?

92
00:05:54,938 --> 00:05:56,565
Bring Father Beocca to me.

93
00:05:57,315 --> 00:05:59,109
I was a little unjust with him...

94
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:02,028
and wish to ask his advice
on a certain person.

95
00:06:02,112 --> 00:06:04,948
Father Beocca has left Winchester, Lady.

96
00:06:05,031 --> 00:06:09,244
He felt there was nothing left here
for him. I doubt he will ever return.

97
00:06:09,327 --> 00:06:11,204
And so our allies abandon us.

98
00:06:11,288 --> 00:06:14,207
Lady, you asked for him to be removed.

99
00:06:15,542 --> 00:06:16,585
Yes.

100
00:06:17,669 --> 00:06:18,962
Yes, I suppose I did.

101
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:23,008
Just as I asked my son to be married
to that vain, silly girl.

102
00:06:24,551 --> 00:06:26,970
Why the Lord guided me this way,
I cannot fathom.

103
00:06:27,596 --> 00:06:28,889
Maybe the Lord didn't.

104
00:06:30,682 --> 00:06:35,896
Any path I chose was to secure
the country my husband loved.

105
00:06:36,646 --> 00:06:38,148
And how well did that work, Lady?

106
00:06:38,172 --> 00:06:46,172
http://hiqve.com/

107
00:07:42,212 --> 00:07:44,756
A pathetic hoard,
most of them drunk or senile.

108
00:07:44,839 --> 00:07:46,591
The Scots will laugh.

109
00:07:46,675 --> 00:07:49,886
I cannot hold them off with this!
We need more warriors.

110
00:07:49,970 --> 00:07:52,681
I have been trying, Lord.

111
00:07:52,764 --> 00:07:55,934
The slaver can get us trained men,
but he wants 10,000.

112
00:07:56,017 --> 00:08:00,188
Ten thousand would empty the treasury.
What good is a fortress without silver?

113
00:08:00,271 --> 00:08:02,899
Lord, we must sell
the heart of Saint Oswald.

114
00:08:04,025 --> 00:08:05,652
Time is moving against us.

115
00:08:07,362 --> 00:08:10,740
We can only sustain these attacks
from the Scots for so long.

116
00:08:11,408 --> 00:08:14,536
He's desperate for it, you say, Aethelred?

117
00:08:14,619 --> 00:08:16,621
This is what I have heard.

118
00:08:16,705 --> 00:08:20,208
The monks he dispatched
will arrive here soon.

119
00:08:26,381 --> 00:08:30,593
Then we shall bleed silver from him
and buy the men.

120
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:09,716
So, where do we start?

121
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:12,594
Where do you look for monks
in a place like this?

122
00:09:13,428 --> 00:09:15,513
- St. Colman's?
- The whorehouse!

123
00:09:17,766 --> 00:09:20,101
That's it. I'm staying on the boat.

124
00:09:20,185 --> 00:09:23,521
It's not safe for you to be alone
this deep within Danelaw.

125
00:09:24,147 --> 00:09:26,524
- Come.
- Then I will pray for salvation.

126
00:09:26,608 --> 00:09:28,485
I will stay with him, keep us both safe.

127
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:31,237
- They do not love a priest in Grimesby.
- Thank you, Father.

128
00:09:32,322 --> 00:09:33,740
To the whorehouse then!

129
00:09:36,409 --> 00:09:38,453
You misjudge your father,
you know.

130
00:09:38,536 --> 00:09:41,498
He's not the bloodthirsty heathen
you take him for.

131
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:44,125
Thou shalt not kill, Father Beocca.

132
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:48,213
- Or are you rusty on the scripture?
- I know the teaching.

133
00:09:48,922 --> 00:09:50,799
But I also know Aelfric.

134
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:54,094
And having some years on you,
I also know...

135
00:09:54,886 --> 00:09:57,847
that sometimes
one must do wrong to do right.

136
00:10:00,350 --> 00:10:04,145
Aelfric tried to kill a child
for no gain but wooden walls.

137
00:10:05,063 --> 00:10:08,608
And for that, he wrenched a boy
from his Christian life...

138
00:10:09,234 --> 00:10:12,362
delivered him to the heathens
and damned his soul to all eternity.

139
00:10:13,321 --> 00:10:16,157
Uhtred is avenging
a great wrong done to him.

140
00:10:17,325 --> 00:10:21,204
Help him in his mission
and you will be helping...

141
00:10:21,287 --> 00:10:23,581
Helping him return to a life
of Christian piety?

142
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:26,334
No.

143
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:29,129
- Not that, but...
- There is a chance.

144
00:10:30,421 --> 00:10:31,965
All sinners can repent.

145
00:10:34,259 --> 00:10:37,053
Well, we shall see.

146
00:10:39,889 --> 00:10:41,266
Come on.

147
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:53,278
Grimesby seems like a lovely place.

148
00:10:53,361 --> 00:10:55,905
I hear the oysters are delicious.

149
00:11:03,371 --> 00:11:06,708
Sihtric, don't make eye contact.

150
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:10,336
- What's your business here?
- We're traders.

151
00:11:11,254 --> 00:11:12,922
We're taking pelts to Frankia.

152
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:14,465
Really?

153
00:11:14,549 --> 00:11:16,402
Well, you keep trouble out of my alehouse,
agreed?

154
00:11:16,426 --> 00:11:19,804
Hey, we're just hungry for some food,
nothing more.

155
00:11:19,888 --> 00:11:22,765
And do you have women? He needs a woman.

156
00:11:22,849 --> 00:11:24,601
We're not that sort of alehouse.

157
00:11:26,477 --> 00:11:27,520
Finan.

158
00:11:32,734 --> 00:11:34,194
She's yours until nightfall.

159
00:11:35,653 --> 00:11:37,447
If you're quick, you can both get a turn.

160
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:40,116
He'll certainly be quick.

161
00:11:44,913 --> 00:11:48,166
Hey, why do I always
have to pretend to be the virgin?

162
00:11:48,249 --> 00:11:50,919
Because no one would
believe I am the virgin.

163
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:55,131
Harder, like your sister does it.

164
00:11:57,467 --> 00:11:58,635
Hit it.

165
00:12:03,306 --> 00:12:06,768
Lead me out to the darkness, Lord.

166
00:12:06,851 --> 00:12:08,645
And let this sin...

167
00:12:08,728 --> 00:12:12,941
- I'm a virgin in that, Lord.
- I'm sure you are, Osferth.

168
00:12:14,025 --> 00:12:15,193
We've found our monks.

169
00:12:15,777 --> 00:12:18,112
Oi, watching costs extra.

170
00:12:21,658 --> 00:12:23,284
Harder!

171
00:12:31,626 --> 00:12:35,797
Traveling overnight, all that way
in the saddle with a red raw ass,

172
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,674
a good thing they like pain!

173
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:40,760
It takes six days to get to Bebbanburg
on the coast road.

174
00:12:40,843 --> 00:12:42,679
They'll get there
before Ascension.

175
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:46,057
I'm a good Christian boy, Lord.

176
00:12:46,975 --> 00:12:48,434
You should not arrive before them.

177
00:12:48,518 --> 00:12:51,312
The rocks around Bebbanburg
do not treat ships kindly.

178
00:12:52,939 --> 00:12:55,650
So, we wait here and enjoy the atmosphere?

179
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:08,538
Uhtred, see these two monks?
They're the ones we've been searching for.

180
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:10,957
They're leaving for Bebbanburg.
Follow them.

181
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:13,459
It's our strongest chance
of getting into the fortress.

182
00:13:14,460 --> 00:13:16,963
- I can't simply follow...
- If there were, I would not ask.

183
00:13:17,046 --> 00:13:20,008
My men have been there recently.
They would be recognized.

184
00:13:20,091 --> 00:13:22,571
- So, I am the sacrificial lamb...
- You are our greatest hope.

185
00:13:23,094 --> 00:13:24,429
Do not do this for me.

186
00:13:24,512 --> 00:13:27,432
Do it for your descendants.
Whatever I take will one day be yours.

187
00:13:27,515 --> 00:13:29,434
I'm not the warrior
you seem to mistake me for.

188
00:13:30,935 --> 00:13:32,270
Why do you have this faith in me?

189
00:13:34,731 --> 00:13:38,067
Because I know that
the spirit of our family is within you.

190
00:13:38,151 --> 00:13:41,404
That will give you a strength
that you do not know yet.

191
00:13:50,038 --> 00:13:52,832
I will try and do as you need,
but I will not kill a man.

192
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:54,208
That is all I want.

193
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:56,961
Three pieces of silver says he runs home.

194
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:03,051
- Take this horse.
- Uhtred.

195
00:14:04,135 --> 00:14:05,970
Ride the road north, close to the shore.

196
00:14:06,054 --> 00:14:08,264
Leave now,
so you can be ahead of the monks.

197
00:14:08,348 --> 00:14:10,183
Find them. Join them.

198
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:18,441
- Lord!
- I would not send you to be slaughtered.

199
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:21,778
When I see you signal,
I will approach the sea gate.

200
00:14:26,199 --> 00:14:27,533
He'll be looked after.

201
00:14:28,117 --> 00:14:30,370
He's blessed, as are you.

202
00:14:30,453 --> 00:14:31,496
All right, come on.

203
00:14:32,455 --> 00:14:33,498
Uhtred.

204
00:15:06,239 --> 00:15:07,490
Try it on.

205
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:11,619
I will, when you leave.

206
00:15:11,702 --> 00:15:13,871
No. I had it made for you.

207
00:15:13,955 --> 00:15:15,164
I want to see it now.

208
00:15:15,248 --> 00:15:18,042
Lord, I will not undress before you.

209
00:15:19,669 --> 00:15:22,505
- I am a woman from a noble family.
- Whose father disgraced...

210
00:15:22,588 --> 00:15:24,388
Whose father
was unfairly shamed for no reason

211
00:15:24,465 --> 00:15:26,426
other than falling
from the Ealdormen's favor.

212
00:15:27,135 --> 00:15:28,845
Lady, enough of this game.

213
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:32,682
You have no good reason to deny me.

214
00:15:32,765 --> 00:15:35,560
I act simply for the good of your soul.

215
00:15:38,146 --> 00:15:39,439
You have a wife.

216
00:15:46,946 --> 00:15:48,114
You are right.

217
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:50,408
I see that now.

218
00:15:53,411 --> 00:15:56,622
I should make myself a widower
and marry you.

219
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:00,251
Is that not what you want?

220
00:16:01,419 --> 00:16:03,629
Along with all of these silks and furs.

221
00:16:04,088 --> 00:16:07,550
Just... a good life...

222
00:16:08,259 --> 00:16:09,886
for a girl who has nothing.

223
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:13,723
Am I being very unfair?

224
00:16:15,516 --> 00:16:17,935
Have I misjudged your Christian soul?

225
00:16:24,859 --> 00:16:26,444
It can all be arranged.

226
00:16:57,892 --> 00:17:00,311
- Did you do the deed?
- No.

227
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:02,813
Drag it out much longer,
he'll lose interest.

228
00:17:02,897 --> 00:17:05,316
How wrong you are.
He's not losing interest.

229
00:17:05,399 --> 00:17:07,319
He's threatening to have
Lady Aethelflaed killed,

230
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:08,486
so that he may marry me.

231
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:10,279
That is good news!

232
00:17:10,363 --> 00:17:14,075
No, it is not! I would have the blood
of Alfred's daughter on my hands.

233
00:17:14,158 --> 00:17:15,344
It seems like a fair exchange.

234
00:17:15,368 --> 00:17:17,411
Married to a man
who kills those who displease him?

235
00:17:17,495 --> 00:17:20,748
- Again, it seems like...
- He is volatile and we must be careful.

236
00:17:21,249 --> 00:17:25,711
Promise me, if he asks you to attack
Lady Aethelflaed, you will refuse.

237
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:31,050
I will never defy the wishes
of King Aethelred.

238
00:17:31,801 --> 00:17:32,843
And nor should you.

239
00:17:44,897 --> 00:17:47,775
We will rest here
and attack at first light.

240
00:17:48,484 --> 00:17:50,528
Catch the Mercians sleeping in their beds.

241
00:17:50,611 --> 00:17:52,154
How far is Aegelesburg?

242
00:17:52,989 --> 00:17:56,325
- Close enough to surprise them.
- Then this is where I say goodbye.

243
00:17:58,661 --> 00:18:01,622
We camp here tonight,
march at dawn!

244
00:18:01,706 --> 00:18:04,041
You are certain
we cannot tempt you to battle?

245
00:18:04,125 --> 00:18:07,461
I have no interest in fighting,
only women and silver.

246
00:18:07,545 --> 00:18:09,589
Because you have to pay women
to hump them?

247
00:18:09,672 --> 00:18:11,882
Better than reeling them in with lies.

248
00:18:12,508 --> 00:18:15,761
Fair. But everything I did
allowed the Danes to triumph.

249
00:18:15,845 --> 00:18:18,556
You will miss a great gathering
of armies, Haesten.

250
00:18:19,223 --> 00:18:22,643
Edward is honor-bound to defend
the land of his sister and mother.

251
00:18:22,727 --> 00:18:25,938
Aethelred's death
will force swift retaliation.

252
00:18:26,022 --> 00:18:27,940
We will ride into Mercia in a fury

253
00:18:28,024 --> 00:18:30,943
and will force them to a battle place
where we have the advantage.

254
00:18:31,027 --> 00:18:34,905
Wessex, Mercians, all Christians.

255
00:18:35,406 --> 00:18:37,199
This will bring them together.

256
00:18:37,283 --> 00:18:39,452
Then you will have united the Saxons.

257
00:18:39,535 --> 00:18:41,537
Alfred would be very proud.

258
00:18:41,621 --> 00:18:43,289
Cnut! Let's go.

259
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:45,583
Boys, come here.

260
00:18:47,877 --> 00:18:50,755
I want you to go with our friend Haesten.

261
00:18:52,131 --> 00:18:55,343
He will take you north
until our campaign is over.

262
00:18:55,426 --> 00:18:58,304
Should they not witness the battle?
I know it's dangerous but...

263
00:18:58,387 --> 00:19:01,307
There will be battles to come.
Today, they are too young.

264
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:07,563
Haesten, attend to them
and teach them nothing you know.

265
00:19:07,647 --> 00:19:10,441
Come, boys, let's get you ready.

266
00:19:11,275 --> 00:19:13,319
The shit loves his offspring.

267
00:19:14,111 --> 00:19:15,696
How did he draw you to him?

268
00:19:16,656 --> 00:19:18,240
We made a bond in blood.

269
00:19:18,324 --> 00:19:21,035
If you ever get bored
of the ugly bastard...

270
00:19:22,036 --> 00:19:24,997
you know, I have fathered ten children.

271
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:28,709
- That is of no use to me.
- No?

272
00:19:30,461 --> 00:19:31,545
No...

273
00:19:32,588 --> 00:19:35,925
because you carry his pup!

274
00:19:39,595 --> 00:19:41,639
I can tell by the tits.

275
00:19:46,060 --> 00:19:49,105
If you tell him this
before I fight the Saxons...

276
00:19:49,647 --> 00:19:52,650
I will cut off your balls
and feed them to you.

277
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:54,443
I'm overjoyed for you, Brida.

278
00:19:55,319 --> 00:19:57,655
The world needs more little Cnuts.

279
00:19:57,738 --> 00:19:58,781
Brida!

280
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:00,074
Come.

281
00:20:01,325 --> 00:20:06,539
Rest tonight. Prepare yourselves.
There will be many sleepless nights ahead!

282
00:20:06,622 --> 00:20:11,669
But, at daybreak,
we shall strike and blood will run!

283
00:20:11,752 --> 00:20:13,838
Mercia will burn!

284
00:20:30,104 --> 00:20:31,564
Bring me Aethelred!

285
00:20:45,745 --> 00:20:47,163
Where is he?

286
00:20:52,293 --> 00:20:53,669
Where's your Lord?

287
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:55,588
Where's your Lord?

288
00:21:01,051 --> 00:21:02,178
Next!

289
00:21:07,516 --> 00:21:08,768
Are there any more?

290
00:21:13,731 --> 00:21:17,318
Could they be mercenaries...
come to help defend us?

291
00:21:17,401 --> 00:21:19,195
A donation from the slaver?

292
00:21:19,695 --> 00:21:23,115
Offering reinforcements
from the goodness of his heart?

293
00:21:23,199 --> 00:21:25,659
Well, perhaps they will turn away.

294
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:29,747
Or they are Scots, returning for a fight.

295
00:21:31,081 --> 00:21:34,043
There is one choice,
though it sickens me to say it.

296
00:21:35,211 --> 00:21:37,129
Pay them to go away.

297
00:21:37,213 --> 00:21:39,340
So they can return again
and we pay them more?

298
00:21:39,423 --> 00:21:41,675
Why not just beg them
to make us their vassals?

299
00:21:41,759 --> 00:21:43,636
I did not say it was a good choice.

300
00:21:47,139 --> 00:21:49,141
Send men out to speak with them.

301
00:21:49,225 --> 00:21:51,101
If they return with heads
on their shoulders,

302
00:21:51,185 --> 00:21:53,145
we know that the Scots might negotiate.

303
00:21:53,229 --> 00:21:57,024
I shall go myself.
I am sick of sending men to slaughter.

304
00:21:58,734 --> 00:22:01,111
Which is why you will never lead, Aidan.

305
00:22:21,799 --> 00:22:22,883
Open the gate.

306
00:22:53,664 --> 00:22:54,999
Alert Lord Aelfric.

307
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:57,209
He'll want to see this.

308
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:34,872
We heard you were drowned.

309
00:23:34,955 --> 00:23:37,750
We were assured.
They said there was no hope.

310
00:23:38,626 --> 00:23:40,169
I nearly did drown, Father.

311
00:23:42,171 --> 00:23:46,008
I believed it was my punishment
for sending you away.

312
00:23:47,051 --> 00:23:48,260
No punishment.

313
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:52,014
Just a moment to learn
how much I wanted to live...

314
00:23:52,932 --> 00:23:54,642
and return to you and Bebbanburg.

315
00:23:54,725 --> 00:23:57,186
I thought my legacy was lost forever.

316
00:23:58,103 --> 00:24:00,356
I assure you,
your descendants will thrive.

317
00:24:01,106 --> 00:24:03,776
When I got word you were under attack,
I seized the moment.

318
00:24:03,859 --> 00:24:05,527
I've brought warriors...

319
00:24:06,528 --> 00:24:09,239
men I've collected
from every corner of the known world.

320
00:24:10,074 --> 00:24:12,409
Strong men, loyal men.

321
00:24:17,665 --> 00:24:19,249
Bebbanburg is saved.

322
00:24:30,636 --> 00:24:32,846
As magnificent as ever it was.

323
00:24:32,930 --> 00:24:36,475
Indeed... if it is real and not a dream.

324
00:24:37,893 --> 00:24:39,436
It is real enough.

325
00:24:41,021 --> 00:24:44,233
- We need get no closer at this point.
- Lord!

326
00:24:45,442 --> 00:24:46,694
Drop the sail!

327
00:24:47,403 --> 00:24:50,614
Row inland
and keep under the shadow of the cliff.

328
00:24:55,536 --> 00:24:57,788
How long do we wait
for your son to send a sign?

329
00:24:58,205 --> 00:24:59,331
Until it comes.

330
00:25:02,251 --> 00:25:04,545
It is all the will of the gods now.

331
00:25:22,896 --> 00:25:25,149
Is this some plan
to become a saint?

332
00:25:26,233 --> 00:25:29,069
It is preparation
for the royal consecration.

333
00:25:29,153 --> 00:25:31,655
Becoming Queen
is a now a holy rite?

334
00:25:31,739 --> 00:25:32,781
The insult of it.

335
00:25:33,532 --> 00:25:36,285
I take it
this was also Lord Aethelhelm's idea.

336
00:25:36,368 --> 00:25:40,497
Yes. He is quiet,
but his ambitions for his family grow.

337
00:25:41,623 --> 00:25:44,710
He obsesses over the aetheling
and pushes me aside.

338
00:25:45,335 --> 00:25:47,087
Had I known what sort of man he was,

339
00:25:47,171 --> 00:25:49,631
I would've selected
a different bride for your brother.

340
00:25:50,132 --> 00:25:51,467
What does the King say?

341
00:25:51,550 --> 00:25:53,510
Edward cherishes peace...

342
00:25:53,969 --> 00:25:56,430
both within Wessex and within the palace.

343
00:25:58,015 --> 00:26:01,393
So, I must accept
when I am no longer wanted.

344
00:26:06,690 --> 00:26:08,859
She feels my father's loss.

345
00:26:09,359 --> 00:26:10,527
As do we all.

346
00:26:17,284 --> 00:26:20,662
I would like 17 candles lit on my behalf.

347
00:26:21,288 --> 00:26:24,750
One at each shrine
and no mumbling in the prayers.

348
00:26:24,833 --> 00:26:27,544
The Lord wants to hear your full hearts.

349
00:26:29,505 --> 00:26:31,090
Seventeen?

350
00:26:31,173 --> 00:26:32,966
Is something on your conscience, Lady?

351
00:26:33,050 --> 00:26:37,387
Many things. I fear I've allowed
too much to change in the palace.

352
00:26:38,347 --> 00:26:42,226
Tell me, the young Centish lady,
Ecgwynn...

353
00:26:42,309 --> 00:26:44,853
The girl who married your son in secret?

354
00:26:45,604 --> 00:26:46,730
Yes.

355
00:26:47,397 --> 00:26:49,650
What do you know of her present situation?

356
00:26:50,943 --> 00:26:54,863
She took holy orders,
when her marriage was forcibly annulled.

357
00:26:55,572 --> 00:26:58,992
And, from what I've heard,
she's very unhappy.

358
00:26:59,660 --> 00:27:03,497
Well, the cloistered life
may not suit a simple girl.

359
00:27:03,580 --> 00:27:06,667
She was forbidden from seeing
the two children she bore your son.

360
00:27:07,584 --> 00:27:09,753
Her daughter she sees occasionally,
but her son...

361
00:27:10,546 --> 00:27:13,048
she's not looked on
since he was taken from her arms.

362
00:27:14,633 --> 00:27:17,386
That seems a cruel punishment.

363
00:27:17,469 --> 00:27:21,348
For the crime of loving Edward
and Edward loving her, yes.

364
00:27:23,308 --> 00:27:26,979
You and Beocca are right
to question my mistreatment of her.

365
00:27:27,062 --> 00:27:30,107
I would like to make amends,
in a small way.

366
00:27:32,860 --> 00:27:35,946
- Where is her son now?
- He lives in a monastery.

367
00:27:36,822 --> 00:27:38,448
So, he has a love of God...

368
00:27:39,366 --> 00:27:40,742
but not that of a mother.

369
00:27:42,119 --> 00:27:44,329
An agony I would not want for my own son.

370
00:27:49,001 --> 00:27:51,461
- I would like to see them both.
- I can have it arranged.

371
00:27:52,045 --> 00:27:55,007
I am presuming you do not want
anyone else to know.

372
00:27:56,425 --> 00:27:58,260
It would put the boy in danger.

373
00:27:59,344 --> 00:28:00,470
We both know that.

374
00:28:30,292 --> 00:28:32,336
Send scouts to look for a battle place.

375
00:28:32,419 --> 00:28:35,339
Make sure the grain stores are emptied
and no food remains.

376
00:28:35,422 --> 00:28:39,009
Gut this palace
before the other Saxons retaliate!

377
00:28:44,389 --> 00:28:47,392
- Did you see the Ealdormen?
- I did.

378
00:28:48,894 --> 00:28:52,272
You're inventive in your cruelty.
Have you found Aethelred?

379
00:28:52,356 --> 00:28:54,650
Not yet. I'm just enjoying his bed.

380
00:28:55,984 --> 00:28:57,069
Would you like to join me?

381
00:29:44,866 --> 00:29:46,910
What are you reading, child?

382
00:29:52,499 --> 00:29:55,085
You are Aethelstan, are you not?

383
00:29:56,128 --> 00:29:57,587
Yes.

384
00:29:57,671 --> 00:30:01,174
Who are your family, Aethelstan?

385
00:30:02,467 --> 00:30:04,553
I've been told not to answer that.

386
00:30:05,804 --> 00:30:09,349
Indeed. That is probably wise.

387
00:30:10,058 --> 00:30:12,311
Are you an abbess, Lady?

388
00:30:12,394 --> 00:30:16,648
No. I am... a friend.

389
00:30:17,274 --> 00:30:22,070
Though many great abbesses feel
I could have been one of their number.

390
00:30:27,367 --> 00:30:29,745
Come with me, Aethelstan.

391
00:30:38,879 --> 00:30:41,882
A lady wants to meet you.

392
00:30:44,801 --> 00:30:46,261
Go to the garden.

393
00:31:51,284 --> 00:31:54,454
- Oh, Lord help us! It is a beggar.
- Don't look at him. Ignore him.

394
00:31:54,538 --> 00:31:57,290
I cannot.
He's heading straight for us.

395
00:31:57,999 --> 00:31:59,042
Travelers!

396
00:32:00,710 --> 00:32:02,170
He looks insane!

397
00:32:02,254 --> 00:32:03,296
Be wary!

398
00:32:04,923 --> 00:32:06,007
Ignore him.

399
00:32:07,300 --> 00:32:10,095
Travelers, this road
is full of murderous thieves!

400
00:32:10,846 --> 00:32:15,183
- Be careful, my brothers in Christ!
- Why do you call us brothers, madman?

401
00:32:15,725 --> 00:32:18,395
- Because I am one of your number.
- You look a beggar.

402
00:32:18,478 --> 00:32:22,482
No! I am a deacon,
cruelly kidnapped from his church.

403
00:32:22,566 --> 00:32:25,402
A boy whose mind is spent
and life is ebbing!

404
00:32:26,695 --> 00:32:29,156
- Let me ride with you.
- We should move on.

405
00:32:29,239 --> 00:32:32,284
In the name of the Virgin,
there are bandits on this road!

406
00:32:32,367 --> 00:32:35,454
Abandon me and I shall perish
and lie here unburied!

407
00:32:35,537 --> 00:32:37,038
Come on.

408
00:32:37,122 --> 00:32:40,292
Please, did Christ not pity the leper?

409
00:32:44,504 --> 00:32:47,841
Please, brothers.
I know about your sins in Grimesby.

410
00:32:50,093 --> 00:32:51,928
Don't let me speak of it to your abbot.

411
00:32:54,639 --> 00:32:55,724
What do you want?

412
00:32:55,807 --> 00:32:59,686
Nothing but traveling companions.
I swear to it, I mean you no harm.

413
00:32:59,769 --> 00:33:02,272
- Are you any good in a fight?
- No.

414
00:33:02,355 --> 00:33:05,817
Good, they can kill you while we escape.

415
00:33:40,227 --> 00:33:42,521
Are you the kind soul
who arranged this meeting?

416
00:33:44,189 --> 00:33:45,232
I am.

417
00:33:46,775 --> 00:33:48,068
Do I know you, madam?

418
00:33:48,151 --> 00:33:53,198
Content yourself with knowing that I am
a mother who feels for your plight.

419
00:33:53,907 --> 00:33:58,119
Then I thank you. To see him even briefly
heals a wounded heart...

420
00:33:59,579 --> 00:34:00,789
for both of us.

421
00:34:01,456 --> 00:34:03,083
You have shown us a great mercy.

422
00:34:04,584 --> 00:34:05,752
Tell me...

423
00:34:07,254 --> 00:34:09,714
am I still out of favor
to the Lady Aelswith?

424
00:34:12,133 --> 00:34:15,220
Lady Aelswith disfavored no one.

425
00:34:16,096 --> 00:34:18,640
She simply chose
what was best for her son...

426
00:34:19,349 --> 00:34:21,184
as you will want the best for yours.

427
00:34:21,268 --> 00:34:23,687
What is best for my son
is what he once had,

428
00:34:23,770 --> 00:34:25,730
a mother and a father living in happiness.

429
00:34:26,523 --> 00:34:31,027
Perhaps. What is done is done.

430
00:34:31,111 --> 00:34:36,241
But yes, it would be foolish for him
to be raised without a woman's nurture.

431
00:34:36,324 --> 00:34:38,952
Men raised by men turn savage.

432
00:34:39,828 --> 00:34:43,540
So we must ensure
there is always a lady to guide him...

433
00:34:44,708 --> 00:34:48,628
when he is permanently moved
to somewhere more secure.

434
00:34:48,712 --> 00:34:50,171
Why must he be moved?

435
00:34:51,923 --> 00:34:56,136
There is concern
that he could be in danger in Wessex.

436
00:34:57,095 --> 00:34:59,848
But rest assured,
he will be well-protected.

437
00:35:01,391 --> 00:35:04,728
But I am afraid you will not be
able to visit again.

438
00:35:11,526 --> 00:35:13,153
Why am I being punished?

439
00:35:14,988 --> 00:35:16,573
Did I deserve this cruelty?

440
00:35:17,616 --> 00:35:19,618
Did I hurt someone as I am now hurt?

441
00:35:20,577 --> 00:35:21,620
Did he?

442
00:35:23,288 --> 00:35:25,707
All'I wanted was a husband and family!

443
00:35:26,291 --> 00:35:29,002
To be with the one I loved
in a quiet place to call home.

444
00:35:29,085 --> 00:35:35,216
Then you would have been unsuited to life
in the palace at Winchester, Ecgwynn.

445
00:35:37,052 --> 00:35:39,471
Which is why this has all come to pass.

446
00:36:09,668 --> 00:36:12,045
- Stop staring at me.
- I'm not staring.

447
00:36:13,380 --> 00:36:17,300
I'm admiring your appetite.
Does death make you hungry?

448
00:36:22,889 --> 00:36:25,058
- Have they found Aethelred?
- Yes.

449
00:36:25,141 --> 00:36:29,187
Good. And where has
that little turd hidden himself?

450
00:36:30,105 --> 00:36:33,274
He's in East Anglia.
He has attacked farms there

451
00:36:33,358 --> 00:36:35,402
and many Danish settlers were killed.

452
00:36:35,485 --> 00:36:37,862
There is no way that fool outwitted us.

453
00:36:37,946 --> 00:36:39,406
It sickens me to say he has.

454
00:36:41,157 --> 00:36:44,327
No...

455
00:36:44,911 --> 00:36:47,122
This was not his doing, but ours.

456
00:36:47,205 --> 00:36:50,083
He thought we were in Irland,
that there would be no reprisals!

457
00:36:50,166 --> 00:36:52,085
We have let this happen, Cnut!

458
00:36:53,294 --> 00:36:55,004
Then we must prevail now.

459
00:36:57,132 --> 00:37:00,343
Farmers and their families
die in war. It's just the way of things.

460
00:37:02,887 --> 00:37:05,724
Danish settlers, Saxon children...

461
00:37:07,350 --> 00:37:08,560
they pay the price.

462
00:37:09,144 --> 00:37:11,813
Besides, if Aethelred
has left his people undefended,

463
00:37:11,896 --> 00:37:15,900
they will be easier to slaughter,
and slaughter will bring Edward sooner.

464
00:38:22,675 --> 00:38:26,721
I knew it! I said this!
I said Cnut was trying to trick us!

465
00:38:26,805 --> 00:38:30,016
- What of Lord Aethelred? Is he dead?
- I will try to find out.

466
00:38:30,099 --> 00:38:33,102
Call off the coronation.
Send men to Aegelesburg to retake it.

467
00:38:33,186 --> 00:38:35,688
No, do not call off
the ceremony...

468
00:38:35,772 --> 00:38:37,649
You cannot
leave the Mercians to their doom.

469
00:38:37,732 --> 00:38:40,318
By the sounds of things,
we're too late.

470
00:38:40,401 --> 00:38:42,320
Send men... you must!

471
00:38:42,403 --> 00:38:46,449
What they did to humiliate the Ealdormen,
Lord King! It must be avenged!

472
00:38:46,533 --> 00:38:49,536
- Lord King...
- They are men of honor, men of my blood!

473
00:38:49,619 --> 00:38:51,955
We should not act in haste.

474
00:38:52,038 --> 00:38:56,376
- Maybe Aethelred's right...
- Edward, you must not delay.

475
00:38:56,459 --> 00:38:57,669
Enough!

476
00:38:58,503 --> 00:39:01,589
I will decide how to respond
to this affront and when!

477
00:39:02,715 --> 00:39:06,386
Not you, nor you,
nor you will set the terms.

478
00:39:09,556 --> 00:39:11,558
And certainly not Cnut.

479
00:40:01,149 --> 00:40:02,317
Hard to tell!

480
00:40:03,651 --> 00:40:05,653
Maybe 40 helmets!

481
00:40:05,737 --> 00:40:09,866
He has put all his men on the ramparts
to make it look like he has more.

482
00:40:10,325 --> 00:40:13,286
- He was always a cunning one.
- Still two against one.

483
00:40:13,369 --> 00:40:17,332
- We're twice as good.
- Yeah, keep saying it, it becomes true.

484
00:40:20,084 --> 00:40:23,046
We don't need to slaughter 'em all,
just hold 'em off.

485
00:40:23,922 --> 00:40:26,633
Lord, the real fight
will be you against Aelfric.

486
00:40:34,140 --> 00:40:35,308
Tell me, Beocca...

487
00:40:37,769 --> 00:40:39,270
is it the right time?

488
00:40:39,896 --> 00:40:41,606
I'm not leading men to defeat?

489
00:40:42,607 --> 00:40:44,275
You are not leading men to defeat.

490
00:40:45,151 --> 00:40:47,779
The fight will be furious. Men will fall.

491
00:40:47,862 --> 00:40:50,239
But I would not encourage you,
if I thought you would lose.

492
00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:53,701
Feel the air here, Uhtred.

493
00:40:54,744 --> 00:40:56,329
Feel its cold breath.

494
00:40:57,789 --> 00:40:59,916
This is the air
that you and I were born to breathe.

495
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:02,460
We're meant to be here.

496
00:41:03,962 --> 00:41:06,047
Let us see if my blood runs thick...

497
00:41:07,465 --> 00:41:08,883
if the signal comes.

498
00:41:14,806 --> 00:41:18,059
- Do you know what that is?
- It's a fort.

499
00:41:18,643 --> 00:41:21,312
Beating heart of this land
they called Bernicia.

500
00:41:22,397 --> 00:41:23,481
Bebbanburg.

501
00:41:25,024 --> 00:41:28,486
The lord who resides here is volatile,
SO be on your guard.

502
00:41:30,321 --> 00:41:33,700
- What if he does not welcome us?
- Then we will not be welcomed home.

503
00:41:34,575 --> 00:41:38,913
And we will be forced to sail to Frisia
to sell your backside in return for food.

504
00:41:54,012 --> 00:41:55,513
It is only monks, Lord.

505
00:41:57,473 --> 00:41:59,434
Aethelred's errand boys.

506
00:42:00,059 --> 00:42:03,021
Let's see how desperate they are
for my holy treasures.

507
00:42:07,150 --> 00:42:09,861
Greetings to Lord Aelfric of Bebbanburg.

508
00:42:10,653 --> 00:42:11,988
I am Brother lestyn.

509
00:42:12,071 --> 00:42:16,159
We are sent by Aethelred of Mercia
to make a trade.

510
00:42:16,743 --> 00:42:18,911
Um, you can turn back.

511
00:42:20,038 --> 00:42:23,624
I've decided I cannot bear to part
with so dear a treasure.

512
00:42:25,626 --> 00:42:28,212
Lord Aethelred will offer a good price.

513
00:42:28,296 --> 00:42:32,341
I put no price on holy relics,
nor should you.

514
00:42:33,009 --> 00:42:37,638
The legacy of my forebears
cannot be measured in silver.

515
00:42:37,722 --> 00:42:41,059
Then might we at least rest
the night here, Lord?

516
00:42:41,142 --> 00:42:43,019
The road has been long.

517
00:42:43,603 --> 00:42:46,022
Perhaps we could discuss the trade.

518
00:42:46,105 --> 00:42:47,648
We are not a lodging house!

519
00:42:49,192 --> 00:42:52,153
Your master has sent you
on a pointless errand.

520
00:42:52,904 --> 00:42:56,574
If Aethelred wishes to reunite
the relics of the beloved saint,

521
00:42:56,657 --> 00:42:59,368
he'll have to fight me for them,
sword to sword.

522
00:43:02,497 --> 00:43:03,581
Lord!

523
00:43:05,124 --> 00:43:09,045
I am but a young man,
but since my childhood, I have heard

524
00:43:09,128 --> 00:43:12,965
that Bebbanburg
was the greatest fortress in the north.

525
00:43:13,049 --> 00:43:17,595
And that its true lord was a man of honor
and great reputation.

526
00:43:17,678 --> 00:43:20,848
Well, who does not take
to a little flattery?

527
00:43:20,932 --> 00:43:22,183
Please, Lord.

528
00:43:23,017 --> 00:43:26,479
I've traveled many weeks
just to admire it.

529
00:43:26,979 --> 00:43:29,732
Reject our plea
to sell us your riches, but...

530
00:43:31,275 --> 00:43:33,236
do not deny my boyhood dream.

531
00:43:39,700 --> 00:43:43,496
Well, I am generous
and a loyal servant to the Church.

532
00:43:43,579 --> 00:43:44,831
So, um...

533
00:43:46,707 --> 00:43:48,000
you are welcome.

534
00:43:49,877 --> 00:43:51,546
Put them in the slave quarters.

535
00:44:07,645 --> 00:44:09,397
Stop looking impressed.

536
00:44:10,148 --> 00:44:11,899
You will push up the price.

537
00:44:25,663 --> 00:44:27,456
- Has he given the signal?
- Lord.

538
00:44:28,082 --> 00:44:29,167
Nothing.

539
00:45:53,709 --> 00:45:55,002
Did you see that?

540
00:46:15,106 --> 00:46:16,440
There, look!

541
00:46:17,984 --> 00:46:19,193
It's the signal!

542
00:46:22,405 --> 00:46:24,323
Move your arses!

543
00:46:25,408 --> 00:46:27,201
Follow us along the rocks.

544
00:46:28,953 --> 00:46:31,414
The rest of you stay here
until I call for the ship.

545
00:47:27,053 --> 00:47:28,679
Which one do you want?

546
00:47:30,306 --> 00:47:31,349
That one.

547
00:47:32,975 --> 00:47:34,018
All yours.

548
00:47:39,482 --> 00:47:41,817
Halt!

549
00:48:03,297 --> 00:48:04,632
Do not move!

550
00:48:07,468 --> 00:48:08,552
Are you there?

551
00:48:12,890 --> 00:48:14,975
Keep this way.
Backs against the wall.

552
00:48:16,060 --> 00:48:17,228
Are you there?

553
00:48:20,147 --> 00:48:21,357
What do we do, Lord?

554
00:48:21,440 --> 00:48:22,942
Do we lift the gate?

555
00:48:23,484 --> 00:48:26,404
- It's worth a try.
- Come on, lift it!

556
00:48:30,324 --> 00:48:33,035
On my count, one, two, three!

557
00:48:34,995 --> 00:48:37,706
Come on! Put your back into it!

558
00:48:37,790 --> 00:48:39,875
Finan, stop. It's too heavy.

559
00:48:39,959 --> 00:48:41,001
Move!

560
00:48:43,754 --> 00:48:46,090
This is a mistake. I was lost!

561
00:48:46,674 --> 00:48:49,468
- You were trying to steal away!
- I was not!

562
00:48:49,552 --> 00:48:51,595
Why? Huh? Why?

563
00:48:59,562 --> 00:49:00,855
Get me those oars.

564
00:49:03,858 --> 00:49:05,067
In there, Osferth.

565
00:49:32,094 --> 00:49:33,762
Put your back into it!

566
00:49:33,846 --> 00:49:37,892
Come on! It's moving! Come on!

567
00:49:41,228 --> 00:49:42,730
Can you get under it, Lord?

568
00:49:50,654 --> 00:49:51,989
A little more.

569
00:49:54,533 --> 00:49:56,076
Go on, Lord!

570
00:50:12,510 --> 00:50:13,844
Summon all to the yard.

571
00:50:15,429 --> 00:50:16,597
Get up!

572
00:50:17,806 --> 00:50:20,142
Let them see how we get thieves
to tell the truth.

573
00:50:24,730 --> 00:50:26,815
Go on, Lord!

574
00:50:26,899 --> 00:50:28,192
Come on!

575
00:50:29,151 --> 00:50:32,154
Heave! Heave!

576
00:50:34,448 --> 00:50:36,450
He's got it!
He's got it! He's got it!

577
00:50:38,077 --> 00:50:39,370
Yes! Yes!

578
00:50:48,045 --> 00:50:51,465
- Is it a trap?
- Is it a trap we can fight our way out of?

579
00:50:57,721 --> 00:51:00,474
Again, who...

580
00:51:00,558 --> 00:51:02,518
do you really...

581
00:51:02,601 --> 00:51:04,019
serve?

582
00:51:04,937 --> 00:51:07,189
My flock and God himself!

583
00:51:12,361 --> 00:51:15,573
- You, what is your mission?
- Simply to...

584
00:51:30,170 --> 00:51:33,215
Must I kill another
before I get the truth?

585
00:51:41,056 --> 00:51:42,850
Let the holy man go free.

586
00:51:43,934 --> 00:51:45,394
He means you no harm!

587
00:52:04,830 --> 00:52:06,749
This one schemes against us, Father.

588
00:52:08,459 --> 00:52:09,668
He is a spy.

589
00:52:30,356 --> 00:52:31,482
We move on.

590
00:52:35,778 --> 00:52:37,071
Who sent you?

591
00:52:39,782 --> 00:52:43,869
You can tell me.
Have the Scots allied with Aethelred?

592
00:52:48,040 --> 00:52:53,462
No recognition in his eyes,
but his face... is familiar somehow.

593
00:52:55,714 --> 00:52:57,174
You are an imposter...

594
00:52:58,550 --> 00:52:59,677
but for whom?

595
00:53:03,180 --> 00:53:04,390
Who are you?

596
00:53:09,978 --> 00:53:12,940
I am Uhtred of Bebbanburg!

597
00:53:20,572 --> 00:53:22,533
It is unwise to mock me.

598
00:53:24,952 --> 00:53:25,994
Kill him.

599
00:53:58,152 --> 00:53:59,570
- Guards...
- Silence!

600
00:54:02,781 --> 00:54:05,576
- Only I shall speak!
- Get back!

601
00:54:07,870 --> 00:54:08,954
Well done!

602
00:54:14,501 --> 00:54:15,669
Do you know who I am?

603
00:54:16,754 --> 00:54:17,880
Hm? Do you know who I am?

604
00:54:20,257 --> 00:54:22,843
I am the true Lord of Bebbanburg!

605
00:54:23,552 --> 00:54:24,970
And I am taking it back!

606
00:54:26,096 --> 00:54:27,681
I have no fight with you.

607
00:54:28,432 --> 00:54:30,100
Only this man is doomed.

608
00:54:31,935 --> 00:54:34,062
Are you happy to see me, Uncle? Huh?

609
00:54:34,146 --> 00:54:37,274
I have waited a lifetime to avenge myself.

610
00:54:38,025 --> 00:54:41,653
I will enjoy taking my time with you! Mm?

611
00:54:42,696 --> 00:54:45,991
No one else will suffer,
if you swear loyalty.

612
00:54:46,074 --> 00:54:49,453
None of you are my enemies.
You are men of Bebbanburg!

613
00:54:49,536 --> 00:54:53,415
And, as Lord of Bebbanburg,
I will provide for and protect you!

614
00:54:55,125 --> 00:55:01,381
And this cruel shit, who has hated you
and mistreated you, will die.

615
00:55:02,508 --> 00:55:04,051
I've come home!

616
00:55:04,134 --> 00:55:07,888
Swear to me and you will have my oath.

617
00:55:13,977 --> 00:55:16,522
Aidan... you remember me?

618
00:55:17,439 --> 00:55:18,690
Who has your allegiance?

619
00:55:29,993 --> 00:55:33,372
I am loyal to the true heir of Bebbanburg.

620
00:55:35,165 --> 00:55:36,250
Good.

621
00:55:36,333 --> 00:55:40,546
Bear witness all,
the true heir of Bebbanburg!

622
00:55:50,806 --> 00:55:51,890
Who are you, boy?

623
00:55:53,016 --> 00:55:55,686
Wihtgar, son of Aelfric.

624
00:55:55,769 --> 00:55:59,189
Very much alive and back at Bebbanburg
as flesh and blood.

625
00:55:59,273 --> 00:56:02,359
And I could kill you with this arrow
in a heartbeat.

626
00:56:04,194 --> 00:56:05,571
You can try.

627
00:56:06,071 --> 00:56:07,489
The arrow would miss.

628
00:56:07,573 --> 00:56:09,908
Then you know nothing
of the weapons of the desert.

629
00:56:09,992 --> 00:56:11,577
Put down the bow.

630
00:56:14,413 --> 00:56:15,914
Put down the bow!

631
00:56:15,998 --> 00:56:19,501
You've lost everything, Osbert!

632
00:56:21,920 --> 00:56:25,048
I won't tell you again, put down the bow!

633
00:56:42,065 --> 00:56:44,192
A son does not always love a father.

634
00:56:45,777 --> 00:56:47,279
Learn from that, fool.

635
00:56:47,362 --> 00:56:49,448
Now, who's with me?

636
00:56:50,824 --> 00:56:53,952
Who is with Wihtgar of Bebbanburg?

637
00:56:55,495 --> 00:56:56,830
Get ready!

638
00:57:05,547 --> 00:57:06,924
Get ready to fight!

639
00:57:06,948 --> 00:57:08,948
http://hiqve.com/

